sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator<br/>Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Training Operator<br/>Controller<br/>(opendatahub ns)
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>OpenShift Monitoring<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Prometheus: Flow 1: Training Job Lifecycle (e.g. PyTorchJob)

    User->>K8sAPI: 1. kubectl apply -f pytorchjob.yaml<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: 2. POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS (TLS auto-managed)<br/>Auth: API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: 2a. Admission Response (allow/deny)
    Note right of Webhook: Validates: DNS-1035 name,<br/>replica types, container images,<br/>elastic policy rules

    K8sAPI-->>User: 2b. Created / Rejected

    Note over Controller: Watch event triggers reconciliation

    K8sAPI->>Controller: 3. Watch notification<br/>PyTorchJob created/updated

    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4a. Create headless Service<br/>{job}-{type}-{idx}<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA token auth
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4b. Create Master Pod<br/>with labels kubeflow.org/operator-name<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA token auth
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4c. Create Worker Pod(s)<br/>with init container (waits for master DNS)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA token auth
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4d. Create NetworkPolicy<br/>(PyTorch only: restricts to same-job pods<br/>+ openshift-monitoring:8080)

    Note over Controller: Expectation controller tracks<br/>expected creates before next reconcile

    activate Controller
    Note right of Controller: Workers: MASTER_ADDR, MASTER_PORT,<br/>WORLD_SIZE, RANK injected
    deactivate Controller

    participant MasterPod as Master Pod<br/>framework-port/TCP
    participant WorkerPod as Worker Pod(s)<br/>framework-port/TCP

    MasterPod->>WorkerPod: 5. Distributed training communication<br/>via headless Service DNS<br/>framework-port/TCP HTTP<br/>No encryption, No auth<br/>(NetworkPolicy restricts to same-job)
    WorkerPod->>MasterPod: 5. Gradient sync / AllReduce<br/>framework-port/TCP HTTP

    Prometheus->>Controller: 6. GET /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>No encryption, No auth
    Controller-->>Prometheus: training_operator_jobs_created_total<br/>training_operator_jobs_successful_total<br/>training_operator_jobs_failed_total

    Note over User,Prometheus: Flow 2: MPI Job Execution (different architecture)

    participant MPIController as Training Operator<br/>MPI Controller
    participant Launcher as MPI Launcher Pod<br/>(init: copies kubectl)
    participant MPIWorker as MPI Worker Pod(s)

    User->>K8sAPI: 1. kubectl apply -f mpijob.yaml
    K8sAPI->>MPIController: Watch: MPIJob created

    MPIController->>K8sAPI: 2a. Create ConfigMap<br/>(hostfile + helper scripts)
    MPIController->>K8sAPI: 2b. Create ServiceAccount<br/>(per-job: mpi-job-{name})
    MPIController->>K8sAPI: 2c. Create Role + RoleBinding<br/>(pods/exec permission)
    MPIController->>K8sAPI: 2d. Create Worker Pods
    MPIController->>K8sAPI: 2e. Create Launcher Pod

    Note over Launcher: Init container copies<br/>kubectl to shared volume

    Launcher->>K8sAPI: 3. kubectl exec to workers<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: per-job SA token
    K8sAPI->>MPIWorker: exec: start MPI process

    MPIWorker->>MPIWorker: 4. MPI inter-process communication<br/>MPI ports/TCP, No encryption
